Commit Message: Started using kubernetes objects for templates
Use chainmap instead of deep merging
Use block style dumps for multiline strings
Added better error message for empty k8s objects
Run Travis CI with Python 3.7 by default (#2)
v1.0: Added support for literal keys, fixed deep merging by replacing chainmap usage.

Allow template() function to return None (#4)

This enables dynamically enabling/disabling a K8s resource

Fixes #3

Enable overriding and extending list value (#5)

With this commit, it's now possible to set a value to a specific item in
a list with the CLI: "kuku render ./templates --set a.0=foo"

Code is a bit tricky, prepare a pen if you want to proof-read it.
Otherwise, reading the unit tests should give a good confidence level.
